Sri Lanka - India T20 International of the Nidahas Trophy will be played from 7 pm today (Mar. 12) at the R. Premadasa Stadium. Sri Lanka side will be led by Thisara Perera after Dinesh Chandimal was suspended for 2 matches over slow over-rate. Along with the 2-match suspension on Sri Lanka's captain, the team's players were fined 60% of their match fee, after ruling that the side fell 4 overs short of their target during their match against Bangladesh on Saturday. Bangladesh captain Mahmudullah, meanwhile, has been fined 20% of his match fee, and the rest of the team 10%, after the side was ruled to have fallen one over short of the time target.